parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cir clip in the transmission can cause the transmission to lock up or explode, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission makes a cracking noise
the transmission locks up
the transmission explodes
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the clip from the transmission shaft can cause unusual noises, transmission failure, and loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unusual cracking noise
especially when making right turns
transmission failure
loss of vehicle power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause a loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially if the stalling occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Engine stalls
loss of vehicle power
unexpected shutdown of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the circlip/C clip in the transmission can cause loud clacking noises, which can be a distraction to the rider and potentially lead to a loss of control.
symptoms: Loud clacking noise when idling or driving
noise disappears when leaning the bike to the left
noise reappears when leaning the bike to the right.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stalling Issue due to Throttle Action
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling issue can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls when downshifting and applying a light quick throttle action
or when accelerating from a stop and applying a light quick throttle action
frequent stalling occurrences.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the luggage compartment latch can cause wear and tear on the locking clasp, leading to eventual total failure, which can result in the loss of personal belongings and compromise the overall structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: The latch on the right luggage bag does not align with the locking clasp
the latch and clasp rub together when closed
the latch wears away at the clasp
the latch eventually "eats" through the clasp
total failure of the luggage compartment latch.
